ce:section.ce:para:
Based on the experimental study and the results of the DMA, an electrochemical simulation model was set up and fitted with the open-source framework Python Battery Mathematical Modelling in version 24.1 (
P y B a M M
) [57]. Furthermore, the Doyle–Fuller–Newman (DFN) model [58,59] was used for the pristine state of the cell and subsequently combined with various degradation models. In agreement with previous work by Oehler et al. [27], we assume an isothermal behavior of the cells at 25 °C due to the large steel fixtures of the cell holders, the large contact area, and the thermal conditioning in an actively controlled climate chamber.
